[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring JNA Configuration**\n\nI'm wondering if I could configure JNA to load a dummy user32 library without needing to edit its metadata. Maybe I can create a test dummy native library. JNA typically loads user32, but I need to ensure it finds a minimal libuser32.so with the necessary symbols. There's a lot to consider, like initializing Ddeml and how JNA resolves symbols at load time. I might create a symlink to libc, but I'm cautious about portability and runtime implications.\n\n**Considering JNA Library Paths**\n\nI'm thinking about using the JNA system property jna.library.path to point to a generated dummy library. However, generating a native library directly in Java tests seems impossible without a compiler, which isn't suitable for my needs. Another option could be to set something like com.sun.jna.Native.POINTER_SIZE, but that may not help. Ultimately, I need to ensure that Ddeml.<clinit> succeeds for everything to work properly, which is a key point in my approach.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cca6e5ebb9c88ce016a10a7a2ece081a0819bcadb7c9984d5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEKe2QoXKe19F6dvA6MIR2pFY9LTJF9CzQgfTbW3tPyVMo7T8JVcuvElVftmqetRJZqIEtzfgHvqtiRflxrfIt66wEiUkEDYrs-HVyWXQuHojRj4KP_Nhhurqgk6fylGLOkAqOqi4KBvMxd7m28lrN8sUeu0IeoFtbbCWnwt-jA6bVq1OXo0ZczY-mENIunZmS_Li9I3BvfrFUQBXCeDTVEcZDNej2TWx-5JbxDp-KtvWC5Pye9WPs0PWxXiKgH3nR2NMpzdD2Gaf2z7gUhPygiD-GfVZHTUJzCqOVMhjpZpYkCWqn8LBqTSIUqhBVTTJShViKiPbOTBljTELwwa1iu997PyC-6-5hqTop8V3t6DvHSEq6b1fKQ7miGrAhlI1CrtyTQG8iT4JbfVOi8d3CRGqGqBIPAOJE76SydIyCEz6Q5SpdtSx4CuufXXeVvyyuqzkbNI8hfkvHxdbJe0OD1DY2xNYVe3DD023BCK1Ti4U4TexVNtu46ANh69Bs8-dSGW_8OdnxlalBjitLe9dfAHQk9mEs3EGp1DMKhM0g96ULEWCxy2CI1fzGG8IQAFRnDjO7ZFCOvNzxbEqon6uZwEIdNupbT3xv_PIQv7L7VQRI5jquLR02tOwnolX5EI9raQhSJTycGSveWAsJq-5H5oIAN1c_IBK-S70CwoKyYLn_CdxU-kEE6o2KjYb1RVBV3ht5ZI9T2L4QIU9nNMz7lQK8ea7UQxbHSVXQKJzxrY-WTJL