[thinking] **Evaluating error handling in tests**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm concerned about catching UnsatisfiedLinkError if the dummy setup fails. If it does, it can pass but might not cover getInt properly. Should I avoid catching it altogether? That seems risky since builds could fail if setup is successful. To ensure we catch failures, maybe not catch errors at all? But if dummy fails to load, we might miss coverage. Perhaps I can adjust to tolerate missing symbols only if makeUser32 fails, but I'd be removing the catch entirely otherwise. It's tricky!
