h the remaining `Field#getInt(...)` call site.\n\nKey change:\n- Before invoking `DdemlException.create(...)` on non-Windows platforms, the test now makes `user32` loadable by creating a temporary `libuser32` symlink/copy pointing at the platform C library and registering it with JNA via `NativeLibrary.addSearchPath(\"user32\", ...)`.\n\nThis allows `Ddeml.<clinit>` to complete during the reflective `Field#getInt(null)` calls in `DdemlException.<clinit>`, so the error-code map can be built and the normal public API behavior can be asserted:\n\n- `getErrorCode()` returns `DMLERR_BUSY`\n- message contains `DMLERR_BUSY`\n- message contains `0x4001`\n\nNo metadata files were edited.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0cca6e5ebb9c88ce016a10a7fa10b481a0ac280e6dd887f3d0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1690, "output": 705, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42331, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779476459510, "responseId": "resp_0cca6e5ebb9c88ce016a10a7ec141081a097eaa271a2637250"}}
